<!doctype html>
<html>

  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <title>{{name}}</title>
    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="//cdn2.hubspot.net/hubfs/1958393/Backgrounds/favicon.ico">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="//aui-cdn.atlassian.com/aui-adg/5.9.6/css/aui.min.css" media="all">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{furl '/css/homepage.css'}}">
    <script src="//ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.8.3/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script src="//aui-cdn.atlassian.com/aui-adg/5.9.6/js/aui.min.js"></script>
  </head>

  <body id="aui-flatpack" class="aui-page-fixed">
    <section id="content" role="main">
      <header class="aui-page-header">
        <div class="aui-page-header-inner">
          <div class="aui-page-header-main intro-header">
            <div class="aui-group">
              <div class="aui-item addon-logo">
                <img src="./img/logo.png" alt="{{name}}">

                <div>
                  <a href="https://www.hipchat.com/addons/install?url={{links.self}}" class="aui-button aui-button-primary"
                     title="Install Nexus for HipChat"><span
                      class="aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-hipchat"></span>
                    Add to HipChat</a>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="aui-item">
                <h1>
                  {{name}}
                  <small class="vendor">By <a href="{{vendor.url}}">{{vendor.name}}</a></small>
                </h1>
                <p class="subtitle">
                  {{description}}
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>
      <div class="aui-page-panel addon-intro-page">
        <div class="aui-page-panel-inner">
          <section class="aui-page-panel-item">
            <div class="aui-group">
              <div class="aui-item">
                <h2>Description</h2>
                <p>
                  Nexus for HipChat consumes Webhooks from Nexus 3 Repository Manager and creates HipChat notifications
                  from their content. It currently supports Created events for both Asset and Component Repository
                  Webhooks. It can be used in hosted repositories to monitor which artifacts are being published;
                  allowing a team to monitor the components they are working on. For proxy repositories, the Nexus
                  Notifier can provide insight as to which new components are being cached into the Repository
                  Manager.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="aui-group">
              <div class="aui-item">
                <h2>Configuration</h2>
                <p>
                  To utilize the Notifier, you must have a running instance of Nexus 3 Repository Manager. Webhooks
                  can be enabled using
                  <a class="aui-button-link"
                     href="//books.sonatype.com/nexus-book/3.0/reference/admin.html#admin-system-capabilities">
                    Nexus Capabilities
                  </a>
                  and enabling the Webhook: Repository Capability. Configure the URL to point to <code>{{links.homepage}}/nexus</code>
                  and set a Secret Key to ensure that the Webhooks received in Nexus for HipChat originated from your
                  Nexus instance.
                </p>
                <h3>Nexus Capability Configuration</h3>
                <img src="./img/nexus-capability.png" alt="Capability Configuration">
                <p>
                  Once Nexus has been configured,
                  <a class="aui-button-link"
                     href="https://www.hipchat.com/addons/install?url={{links.self}}">
                    install
                  </a>
                  Nexus for HipChat. In order to configure Nexus for HipChat you need to determine the Node ID of
                  your Nexus server. This is available in the Node: Identify capability settings, under Description
                  and Node ID.
                </p>
                <h3>Nexus Node: Identity</h3>
                <img src="./img/nexus-node-id.png" alt="Nexus Node ID">
                <p>
                  Fill out the Nexus Node ID and Secret Key from the previous steps. A Regex Filter can be used to
                  filter the notifications by the component or asset which triggered the event.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="aui-group">
              <div class="aui-item">
                <h2>Contributing</h2>
                The source code for this addon is kept on GitHub at
                <a class="aui-button-link"
                   href="//github.com/sonatype/nexus-hipchat-notifier">
                  sonatype/nexus-hipchat-notifier
                </a>. It is licensed under Apache License, Version 2.0 and contributions are welcome through forks
                and pull requests. Code should be formatted according to the Sonatype Code Styles available at
                <a class="aui-button-link"
                   href="//github.com/sonatype/codestyle">
                  sonatype/codestyle
                </a>.
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>
        </div>
        <footer id="footer" role="contentinfo">
          <section class="footer-body">
            <ul id="aui-footer-list">
              <li><a href="https://hipchat.com">HipChat</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://developer.atlassian.com/hipchat">Developers</a></li>
              <li>Copyright Â© 2016 Atlassian</li>
            </ul>
            <div id="footer-logo"><a href="http://www.atlassian.com/">Atlassian</a></div>
          </section>
        </footer>
      </div>
    </section>
  </body>

</html>
